rComments: I had Professor Poulin for DCC2118 and DCC2119 during the pandemic and he was by far my favourite prof. You can tell he wants his students to succeed, and the way he teaches always kept me genuinely engaged in the material. His assignments were fair, and clearly reflected each course. Highly recommend taking his classes if you have the chance!

Daniel Poulin is most people's favorite prof (people who had him of course). He is great, he cares, he puts a lot of love in his teaching and is always available to his students. During the pandemic, attending his class was something I could look forward to. Daniel, if you're reading this, you rock.

I love Professor Poulin! I think he's an absolute gem. He is so sweet and kind. He cares deeply about his students and is an amazing professor. He also gives useful feedback and prepares you not only for exams but life. He will take his own time just to help you out. If I could hug him for a second of my life, I would be good for the rest of it.

He is one of the kindest professors. He is understanding and does everything to make the class easier on the students. He is passionate about what he teaches and he wants his students to understand. He explains topics clearly. You will need to work, rewatching lectures, and take thorough notes, but it is possible to do well in his class.

He is by far the best professor I've ever had at uOttawa. Gives a great lecture, easy grader, exam is open-book!He really connects with his students, and spends half the class telling stories about his wife, kids, and dogs. Would strongly recommend.
Excellent professor. Makes a subject that could be considered boring, quite interesting (or at least tolerable) -- highly recommend!
